# Store text files with LF in the repo, regardless of the committer's OS.
#
# Why: the daily-refresh GitHub Action runs on a Linux runner. Without this,
# index.html was stored with CRLF (committed from Windows), the runner rewrote
# it as LF, and `git diff` then reported the WHOLE file as changed — tripping
# the script's MAX_DIFF_LINES guard and failing the refresh ~1/3 of days.
# Pinning text to LF keeps daily diffs to the handful of lines that really change.
* text=auto eol=lf
*.html text eol=lf
*.js   text eol=lf
*.py   text eol=lf
*.yml  text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
*.md   text eol=lf
*.css  text eol=lf
*.toml text eol=lf
